article.description: — Kentrell Pullian scored 18 points as Milwaukee beat IUPUI 74-61 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Pullian scores 18 as Milwaukee downs IUPUI 74-61
article.linkText: Pullian scores 18 as Milwaukee downs IUPUI 74-61
article.story: MILWAUKEE, Wisc. -- — Kentrell Pullian scored 18 points as Milwaukee beat IUPUI 74-61 on Saturday night. Pullian shot 6 for 11, including 4 for 8 from beyond the arc for the Panthers (7-3). Markeith Browning II scored 12 points while going 4 of 9 and 4 of 4 from the free throw line. Justin Thomas finished 4 of 6 from the field to finish with 11 points. Vincent Brady II led the way for the Jaguars (1-7) with 18 points. IUPUI also got 10 points and seven assists from Jlynn Counter. In addition, Daylan Hamilton had six points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
